    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-27T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-27T07:00:00-05:00" n="879"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d879">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">681.003/199: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-27T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >July 27, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received July 27—8:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. Your No. 48, July 14 [<hi rend="italic">24</hi>], 4 p.m. Foreign Office
                    states reply has at length been received from Spanish High Commissioner which is
                    not entirely satisfactory. Foreign Office, however, favors settlement, and has
                    placed matter before Prime Minister urging speedy decision.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
